o it in two passes, while the GC can do it in one. I'd be surprised to see Doom 3 on GC, but I dop suspect that someone will come up with similarly creative uses for textures on it.<br><br>The X-box has the harddrive, which is a huge plus for heavy simulation gameplay that requires lot's of details to be stored(Like Morrowind), but it also opens up for patching(God forbid). Alarmingly there has been some reports of small bugs in X-Box Morrowind, but nothing showstopping.<br><br>But... the day that Microsoft decides to release a patch for an X-Box game, is the day it will all fall down. Hope it doesn't happen, and that they will just pull the game of the shelves if it has crucial bugs.<br><br>All three machines are good, but Nintendo is the only games company left in the industry. These large corporations are a bit scary, politically and for the games themselves.<br>While Nintendo lives on how good games they make, Sony and Microsoft are playing at many more strings.<br>Theoretically, if Sony's TV division goes to hell, the effects will be felt even on PS2, and if Microsoft suddenly messes up with Windows sales, then that will effect the X-Box.<br><br>Nintendo is about games.<br><br>Not about baseball caps.<br><br>If anyone wonders which of the machines to buy.... then buy all three.... But the Gamecube first. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upunisherx666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Punisher X 666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 10:12:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gamegen.com/fightgen/characters/wangtang-q4.jpg width=124 height=140></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slagging X-BOX and PS2!</span><hr size=1> I don't we