idth=64 height=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slagging X-BOX and PS2!</span><hr size=1> I dont see how having a console company that makes games makes the console better, just look at the Saturn and the N64. It might have good first party games but thats not all that people play, theres a lot of 3rd party developers that are much better at making games than Nintendo.<br><br>What matters is the console, not the company that makes it. <p><a href="http://www.newelysium.com"><img src="http://www.newelysium.com/banners/button1.gif" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubasseex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Basse Ex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 2:35:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://basse.ex.50megs.com/images/kimleliten.jpg width=125 height=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slagging X-BOX and PS2!</span><hr size=1> It's a matter of focus. Neither Microsoft nor Sony are in a position to focus as much on games as Nintendo. Nintendo stakes it's pride on games.<br><br>In all other fields where big multi-corporations have squashed the specialists companies of that field, there has been a degradation of quality once the specialist competitors are out of the field, and the multi-corporations are free to reign.<br><br>Simply because you cannot focus as much on one ball, when you're juggling 5 of them.<br><br>Nintendo is important because it doesn't allow Sony and Microsoft to slack off. It keeps them on edge. You have to be on edge when competing with a specialist.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ushousetsu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shousetsu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.newelysium.com/forum/psicon.gif width=13 height=13" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 2:53:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.newelysium.com/forum/photo2.jpg width=64 height=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slagging X-BOX and PS2!</span><hr size=1> no, they have their own divisions. Just like how Nintendo has its own divisions for software and hardware. Its as if they are split up into their own individual companies.<br><br>Sony doesnt make PS2's and cd players with the same division. So their focus isnt being split up. If buisness worked like the way you are talking then it would be way to chaotic to do anything other than one product.<br><br>Just ask Pat how the X-Box team works. They have very little, if any contact with the other Microsoft parts like Windows.<br><br>They actually are focusing on their own specialty, the PS2 people dont have to worry about the Sony Wega people or vice versa <p><a href="http://www.newelysium.com"><img src="http://www.newelysium.com/banners/button1.gif" border=0></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ushousetsu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shousetsu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.newelysium.com/forum/psicon.gif width=13 height=13" BORDER=0> at: 6/18/02 2:54:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubasseex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Basse Ex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 3:46:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://basse.ex.50megs.com/images/kimleliten.jpg width=125 height=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slagging X-BOX and PS2!</span><hr size=1> yes, they have division, but the company as a whole is focused on games, and games-related stuff.<br><br>Yes, the folks at the X-box team are focused and dedicated, they're gamers, and know their hats, but they are still subject to the main(?) corporation. When the main(?) corporation decides that games aren't in such high demand\competition, they have the power to cut funds or channel money.<br><br>That's the way multi-corporations work.<br><br>I, for one, value tradition. Nintendo is a part of the cultural history of games.<br>Nintendo is about games. If they don't make games, there is no Nintendo. <br><br>Sony(Not specifically the PS2 team) and Microsoft(Not specifically the X-Box team) is in a completely different ballgame. <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ushousetsu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shousetsu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.newelysium.com/forum/psicon.gif width=13 height=13" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 4:35:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.newelysium.com/forum/photo2.jpg width=64 height=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slagging X-BOX and PS2!</span><hr size=1> That hasnt happened before though so I dont see what the problem is. Games are growing faster than ever and I cant imagine them thinking that its a good idea to pull the plug.<br><br>Also since they are part of a major corporation of different products they will always have money coming in. If Nintendo is suffering then they dont have a backup flow of money (ie Sega), if their sales suffer then theyre finished like how the 64 became a door stop after the first year. If the PS2 and X-box suffer then they will get more money to advertise, offer more things, and get more games on the system.<br><br>A company that offers everything is obviously more safe than a company that offers one thing. <p><a href="http://www.newelysium.com"><img src="http://www.newelysium.com/banners/button1.gif" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uascendedbob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ascended Bob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 5:26:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slagging X-BOX and PS2!</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry if I sounded disrespectful to hats. I love hats and still plan to get a GC. Its just that Visors and Baseball caps started looking really good after the N64 and Dreamcast hats fell off. The N64 totally ate balls. So I bought a playstation. Now I've got a PS2. I don't see how just because Nintendo is a traditional game company that makes them better. And they're not just sticking to games. They make a gripload of cash with their child targeted Pokemon and Hamtaro animes. So even they see the benefit of having a backup plan. Or at leas subsidiaries to add to the parent company's money-pot. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=224.topic&start=21&stop=38>2</